Then Boost Libraries version 1.81.0 is installed from the given source. Since these are just the libraries, we have put them inside the Sword project directory as it is ambiguous from the SWROD documentation regarding the path of these Boost Library files.
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro SwordBuild % cd boost_1_81_0
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro boost_1_81_0 % ls
INSTALL		LICENSE_1_0.txt	boost		boost.css	boostcpp.jam	bootstrap.sh	index.htm	libs		rst.css		tools
Jamroot		README.md	boost-build.jam	boost.png	bootstrap.bat	doc		index.html	more		status
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro boost_1_81_0 %  
https://boostorg.jfrog.io/artifactory/main/release/1.81.0/source/
Last past of the pre-requisites is to have a Ninja build system post which we can go ahead with the SWORD installation. For that, we cloned the Ninja git repo and executed the binaries.
https://github.com/ninja-build/ninja
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro SwordBuild % git clone <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/ninja-build/ninja" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/ninja-build/ninja</a>
