Now we tried to install SWORD as suggested in the documentation but we ran into errors as shown below:
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro SwordBuild % cd openmp/runtime/build 
pavanik@Pavanis-MacBook-Pro build % cmake -G Ninja \
 -D CMAKE_C_COMPILER=clang \
 -D CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=clang++ \
 -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
 -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=$OPENMP_INSTALL \
 ..
ninja -j8 -l8                             # or any number of available cores
ninja install
CMake Warning (dev) in CMakeLists.txt:
  No project() command is present.  The top-level CMakeLists.txt file must
  contain a literal, direct call to the project() command.  Add a line of
  code such as

    project(ProjectName)

  near the top of the file, but after cmake_minimum_required().

  CMake is pretending there is a "project(Project)" command on the first
  line.
This warning is for project developers.  Use -Wno-dev to suppress it.

